{"lemma":"كُبْرُ","slug":"كُبْرُ","root":"ك.ب.ر","root_slug":"ك-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كُبْرُ","root":"كبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":11,"pos_tags":["name","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":21},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36563","n36564","n36568","n36569","n36570","n36571","n36572","n36573"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become big","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to grow, to grow up","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become famous","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become too great (for something)","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be too proud, to snub, to disdain","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become too oppressive, to appear intolerable, to become too difficult, to become troublesome","tags":["stative"],"examples":[{"text":"وَإِن كَانَ كَبُرَ عَلَيْكَ إِعْرَاضُهُمْ فَإِنِ ٱسْتَطَعْتَ أَن تَبْتَغِيَ نَفَقًا فِي ٱلْأَرْضِ أَوْ سُلَّمًا فِي ٱلسَّمَاءِ فَتَأْتِيَهُم بِآيَةٍ","english":"And if their aversion is grievous unto thee, then, if thou canst, seek a way down into the earth or a ladder unto the sky that thou mayst bring unto them a portent (to convince them all)!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَبُرَ (kabura) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be older than","tags":["stative","transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"يَكْبُرُ أَخَاهُ بِعَامَيْنِ","english":"He is two years older than his brother"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَبَرَ (kabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","stative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enlarge, to make something bigger","tags":["causative","stative","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to say اَللّٰهُ أَكْبَر (allāhu ʔakbar, “God is greatest”)","tags":["intransitive","stative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"great calamities","tags":["stative"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنَّهَا لَإِحْدَى الْكُبَرِ","english":"Lo! this is one of the greatest (portents)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"greatness, largeness","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"magnificence, majesty","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"old age","tags":["stative"],"examples":[{"text":"أَيَوَدُّ أَحَدُكُمْ أَن تَكُونَ لَهُ جَنَّةٌ مِّن نَّخِيلٍ وَأَعْنَابٍ تَجْرِي مِن تَحْتِهَا ٱلْأَنْهَـٰرُ لَهُ فِيهَا مِن كُلِّ ٱلثَّمَرَٰتِ وَأَصَابَهُ ٱلْكِبَرُ وَلَهُ ذُرِّيَّةٌ ضُعَفَآءُ فَأَصَابَهَآ إِعْصَارٌ فِيهِ نَارٌ فَٱحْتَرَقَتْ","english":"Would any of you like to have a garden of palm-trees and vines, with rivers flowing underneath it, with all kinds of fruit for him therein; and old age hath stricken him and he hath feeble offspring; and a fiery whirlwind striketh it and it is (all) consumed by fire."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"majesty, glory, highness","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pride, presumptuosity, superciliousness, haughtiness, greed for glory","tags":["stative"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ ٱلَّذِينَ يُجَـٰدِلُونَ فِي ءَايَـٰتِ ٱللَّهِ بِغَيْرِ سُلْطَـٰنٍ أَتَىٰهُمْ إِن فِي صُدُورِهِمْ إِلَّا كِبْرٌ مَّا هُم بِبَـٰلِغِيهِ","english":"Lo! those who wrangle concerning the revelations of Allah without a warrant having come unto them, there is naught else in their breasts save pride which they will never attain."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"leonine share, greatest deal, bulk","tags":["stative"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنَّ ٱلَّذِينَ جَآءُو بِٱلْإِفْكِ عُصْبَةٌ مِّنْكُمْ لَا تَحْسَبُوهُ شَرًّا لَّكُم بَلْ هُوَ خَيْرٌ لَّكُمْ لِكُلِّ ٱمْرِئٍ مِّنْهُم مَّا ٱكْتَسَبَ مِنَ ٱلْإِثْمِ وَٱلَّذِي تَوَلَّى كِبْرَهُ مِنْهُمْ لَهُ عَذَابٌ عَظِيمٌ","english":"Lo! they who spread the slander are a gang among you. Deem it not a bad thing for you; nay, it is good for you. Unto every man of them (will be paid) that which he hath earned of the sin; and as for him among them who had the greater share therein, his will be an awful doom."}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Kubbar, an uninhabited island in the Bay of Kuwait","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"caper (Capparis gen. and especially Capparis spinosa, as well as the edible buds from it)","tags":["stative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drum, timbrel","tags":["obsolete","stative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Inherited from Proto-Semitic *kabar- together with Hebrew כָּבַר (kāḇár, “to be great, to become great; to be many, to multiply”), Akkadian kabārum (“to be or become thick”) etc.\n\nBorrowed from Ge'ez ክብር (kəbr), see كِبْرِيَاء (kibriyāʔ).\n\nFrom Classical Syriac ܩܦܪ (qappar, qappār, “caper-bush”) or Classical Syriac ܟܦܪ (kappar, kappār), considered from Ancient Greek κάππαρις (kápparis) of uncertain likely Asian origin.\nFor the variation a ⇌ ā in Aramaisms, compare سُكَّر (sukkar), سُكَّار (sukkār, “bolt-lock”) and قُنْبَر (qunbar), قُنْبَار (qunbār), كُنْبَار (kunbār, “coir”).\n\nBorrowed from Ge'ez ከበሮ (käbäro, “drum, timbrel”)."},"ipa":["/ka.bu.ra/","/ˈkɪbɐr/","/ˈkibir/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36563","headword_ar":"كَبُرَ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuborN","text_ar":"كُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kibarN","text_ar":"كِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabaArapN","text_ar":"كَبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large in body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corporeal substance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in years,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"age;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(when said of a human being, often particularly signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he attained to puberty;"},{"kind":"text","text":") and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dagura","text_ar":"ضَغُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZuma","text_ar":"عَظُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasuma","text_ar":"جَسُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [In the K the pret. is twice mentioned: where it is explained as signifying the contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sagura","text_ar":"صَغُرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the above inf. ns. are mentioned, as in the A: where it is explained by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZuma","text_ar":"عَظُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasuma","text_ar":"جَسُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K, no inf. n. is mentioned; but in the TA it is there said that in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZuma","text_ar":"عَظُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"it relates to an affair or case, and that the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kibarN","text_ar":"كِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabaArapN","text_ar":"كَبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and that in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasuma","text_ar":"جَسُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"it relates to anything.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabura AlA^amoru","text_ar":"كَبُرَ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, of great moment; it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, momentous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it signifies as in the phrase next following]. (A.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabura Ealayohi AlA^amoru","text_ar":"كَبُرَ عَلَيْهِ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, difficult, hard, severe, grievous, distressing, afflictive, troublesome,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burdensome, to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its effect upon him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~a","text_ar":"شَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, * TA.) In this sense the verb is used in the Kur, x, 72, (TA,) and xlii, 11. (Bd, ii. 42.) And so in the Kur again, xvii, 53,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awo xaloqFA mim~aA","text_ar":"اَوْ خَلْقًا مِمَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakoburu fiY Sduwrikumo","text_ar":"يَكْبُرُ فِى صدُورِكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awoxaloqFA mim~aA","text_ar":"اَوْخَلْقًا مِمَّا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakoburu Einodakumo Eano qubuwli AlHayaApi","text_ar":"يَكْبُرُ عِنْدَكُمْ عَنْ قُبُولِ الحَيَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Or a created thing of those which are too difficult in your minds to receive life"},{"kind":"text","text":"], as being the thing most remote from capability to receive life. (Bd.) [This signification is from the primary application of the verb.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabira","text_ar":"كَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kibarN","text_ar":"كِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makobirN","text_ar":"مَكْبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, a human being, and a beast, TA, and a child, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became full-grown,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advanced in age."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) Hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabira Eamoruw Eani AlT~awoqi","text_ar":"كَبِرَ عَمْرُو عَنِ الطَّوْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Twq","text_ar":"طوق"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [In modern Arabic, and, I believe, sometimes, in classic authors, it also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became big;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(said of a boy, or child, in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rE","text_ar":"رع"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. e. attained to full growth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to adolescence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to puberty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabiyrN","text_ar":"كَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] This form of the verb and that first mentioned are sometimes erroneously used, each for the other, by persons of distinction as well as by the vulgar. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaborapN","text_ar":"كَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAbarotuhu fakabarotuhu","text_ar":"كَابَرْتُهُ فَكَبَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. of the latter,"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 3. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabarahu bisanapK","text_ar":"كَبَرَهُ بِسَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exceeded me in age by a year."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kabaraniY A_il~aA bisanapK","text_ar":"مَا كَبَرَنِى اـِلَّا بِسَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did not exceed me in age save by a year."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n36564","headword_ar":"كبّر","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkabiyrN","text_ar":"تكَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He magnified,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honoured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZ~ama","text_ar":"عَظَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S) ―         -b3-  Also, inf. n. as above, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kib~aArN","text_ar":"كِبَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sgh, K,) which latter is of the dial. of Belhárith Ibn-Kaab and many of the people of El-Yemen, (Sgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu A^akobar","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akobaru","text_ar":"اَكْبَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below."}],"source_refs":["S","Sgh","K"]},{"entry_id":"n36568","headword_ar":"كُبْرٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborN","text_ar":"كِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two senses:       -A2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborapN","text_ar":"كِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in three places."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2586}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n36569","headword_ar":"كِبْرٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Greatness"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in corporeal substance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IKoot, Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nobility; eminence; highness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuborN","text_ar":"كُبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"highness, in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to, nobility;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuburN","text_ar":"كُبُرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZamapN","text_ar":"عَظَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which, as an attribute of God, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"majesty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munakab~irN","text_ar":"مُنَكَبِّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and as an attribute of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pride"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb, K:) a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~akab~uru","text_ar":"التَّكَبُّرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiboriyaA='u","text_ar":"كِبْرِيَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) a word, says Kr, of which there is not the like [in measure], except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siymiyaA='u","text_ar":"سِيمِيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jirobiyaA='u","text_ar":"جِرْبِيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for, he adds, as to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiymiyaA='u","text_ar":"كِيمِيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I think it a foreign word: (TA:) the latter [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiboriyaA'u","text_ar":"كِبْرِيَاءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] occurs as an attribute of God, in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaZamapN","text_ar":"عَظَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Mgh, Jel,) in the Kur, xlv. 36: (Jel:) and as an attribute of men, in the Kur, x. 79, where it is said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proud behaviour towards others,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dominion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAmb, Bd, Jel:) and both signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pride, haughtiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self-admiration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self-conceit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holding one's self greater than others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the ↓ latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disdain of submission;"},{"kind":"text","text":"an attribute to which none but God has a right. (El-Basáïr.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unbelief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"association of any other being with God."},{"kind":"text","text":"So in a trad., in which it is said, that he who has in his heart the weight of a grain of mustard-seed of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kibor","text_ar":"كِبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"shall not enter paradise. (TA.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabiyrapN","text_ar":"كَبِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"main,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greatest, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; (Fr. ISk, Az, S, Mgh, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuborN","text_ar":"كُبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, Mgh, Sgh, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuZomN","text_ar":"عُظْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Fr;) thought by Ibn-ElYezeedee to be a dial. form; but Az says, that the Arabs used the other form ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborN","text_ar":"كِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) So in the Kur, xxiv. 11,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l~a*iY tawal~aY kiborahu","text_ar":"وَا@لَّذِى تَوَلَّى كِبْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he who took upon himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertook, the main part thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, of the very wicked lie against 'Áïsheh: (Jel:) thus accord. to the “ Seven Readers ”: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuborahu","text_ar":"كُبْرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is an extr. reading, (Msb,) the reading of Homeyd Ibn-El-Aaraj, (Fr, Sgh,) and of Yaakoob. (Sgh, Bd.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuboru siyaAsapi Aln~aAsi fiY AlmaAli","text_ar":"كُبْرُ سِيَاسَةِ النَّاسِ فِى المَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [app. signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The main part of men's management is with respect to property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","S","Msb","TA","A","Mgh","Jel","Bd","IAmb","Fr","Sgh"]},{"entry_id":"n36570","headword_ar":"كَبَرٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"capparis"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linnæus;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant having thorns;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) an arabicized word, from the Persian ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabaro","text_ar":"كَبَرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S;) called in Arabic"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laSafN","text_ar":"لَصَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSafN","text_ar":"اَصَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) the vulgar say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kub~aArN","text_ar":"كُبَّارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) A beverage is described as made of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kabar","text_ar":"كَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and barley:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kvr","text_ar":"كثر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistranscription. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n36571","headword_ar":"كُبُرٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborN","text_ar":"كِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n36572","headword_ar":"كِبَرٌ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1: ―         -b2-  see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaborapN","text_ar":"كَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n36573","headword_ar":"كُبُرٌّ","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiborapN","text_ar":"كِبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}